(61, 1, '2012-04-20 17:06:57', '2012-04-20 11:36:57', '', 'Associate Domain', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', 'associate', '', '', '2012-04-20 17:06:57', '2012-04-20 11:36:57', '', 58, 'http://v6.cometchat.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2012/04/associate.png', 0, 'attachment', 'image/png', 0),
(62, 1, '2011-05-14 14:53:21', '2011-05-14 09:23:21', '# Overview\n\nPlugins are of two types:\n\n1. To enhance one-on-one chat functionality\n2. To enhance chatroom functionality\n\n# One-on-one chat plugins\n\nOne-on-one chat plugins add new features to the one-on-one chat box. In other words, when the user of your site chats with another user using the chat box on the right side, he/she can have a better chatting experience with the help of these plugins \ne.g. audio/video chat, screen-sharing etc. are examples of one-on-one chat.\n\n# Chatroom plugins\n\nChatroom plugins add new functionality to chat rooms. You can add plugins like video conference, screen-sharing, white-board etc. to chatrooms. All plugins available for one-on-one chat cannot be added to chatrooms but most plugins are common with one difference. In one-on-one chat, these plugins are used between two users. In chatrooms, they are used by multiple users at the same time.', 'Plugins', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'plugins', '', '', '2011-05-14 14:53:21', '2011-05-14 09:23:21', '', 4441, 'http://www.cometchat.com/documentation/?page_id=62', 34, 'page', '', 0),
(63, 1, '2011-09-22 21:32:23', '2011-09-22 16:02:23', '', 'rsz_facebookgtalkchat', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', 'rsz_facebookgtalkchat', '', '', '2011-09-22 21:32:23', '2011-09-22 16:02:23', '', 51, 'http://v6.cometchat.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/rsz_facebookgtalkchat.jpg', 0, 'attachment', 'image/jpeg', 0),
(64, 1, '2011-05-14 15:02:55', '2011-05-14 09:32:55', '# One-on-One Plugins\n\nTo activate one-on-one plugins, you need to go to *CometChat Admin Panel -&gt; Plugins*\n\nThe center panel shows plugins that are currently live on your site and available plugins shows the list of plugins that you can add to CometChat. To change the order, you can simply move the plugins vertically.\n\n![Plugins1]\n(http://v6.cometchat.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2012/04/pluginnew1.png)\n\n# Chatroom Plugins\n\nTo activate chatroom plugins, you need to go to *CometChat Admin Panel -&gt; Plugins -&gt; Chatroom plugins*.\n\nChatroom plugins must be configured using the One-on-One plugins page. There is no configuration option in the chatroom plugins page.\n\n![Chatroom - Plugins]\n(http://v6.cometchat.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2012/04/Chat+plguins1.png)\n\n&gt; Clear your browser cache completely to view changes after any modifications. Your browser may cache the output of the JS file and thus you may not be able to view the added plugins until you clear your browser cache.', 'Activating Plugins', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'activating-plugins', '', '', '2011-05-14 15:02:55', '2011-05-14 09:32:55', '', 62, 'http://www.cometchat.com/documentation/?page_id=64', 5, 'page', '', 0),
(65, 1, '2012-04-20 17:12:23', '2012-04-20 11:42:23', 'Along with adding keys, you need to update your <strong>App Domain</strong> and <strong>Mobile Web URL</strong> in your Facebook Application settings.\n\nApp Domain: chatforyoursite.com\nMobile Web URL: http://chatforyoursite.com\n\n<img src="http://v6.cometchat.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2013/02/applicationsettings.jpg" alt="Facebook Application Settings" />\n\n<blockquote>"chatforyoursite.com" is a domain that we own and use to enable the Facebook chat feature.<br /><br />Do not rename "chatforyoursite.com" to "chatforYOURSITENAME.com". Please enter it as-is. It is meant to be "chatforyoursite.com".</blockquote>\n\nTo learn more, refer to our <a href="http://www.cometchat.com/documentation/admin/extensions/facebook-gtalk-extension" target="_blank">configuring your Facebook Application</a> guide.', 'I entered my Facebook application keys in the Facebook/Gtalk settings and Facebook Connect option disappeared', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'i-entered-my-facebook-application-keys-in-the-facebookgtalk-settings-and-facebook-connect-option-disappeared', '', '', '2012-04-20 17:12:23', '2012-04-20 11:42:23', '', 0, 'http://www.cometchat.com/answers/?p=65', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(66, 1, '2012-04-20 17:12:05', '2012-04-20 11:42:05', '', 'Facebook Application Settings', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', 'applicationsettings', '', '', '2012-04-20 17:12:05', '2012-04-20 11:42:05', '', 65, 'http://v6.cometchat.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2012/04/applicationsettings.jpg', 0, 'attachment', 'image/jpeg', 0),
(68, 1, '2012-04-21 12:24:49', '2012-04-21 06:54:49', 'Manually edit the file <strong>module/profile/template/default/block/header.html.php</strong> or using your phpFox Admin Panel, go to:\n\nExtensions -&gt; Theme -&gt; Manage Theme -&gt; YOURTHEME -&gt; Edit Templates -&gt; Profile -&gt; header.html.php \n\nFind the following code:\n\n<pre><code>{if isset($aUser.is_online) &amp;&amp; $aUser.is_online &amp;&amp; Phpfox::isModule(''im'') &amp;&amp; Phpfox::getParam(''im.enable_im_in_footer_bar'') &amp;&amp; $aUser.is_friend == 1}\n            &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;#&quot; onclick=&quot;$.ajaxCall(''im.chat'', ''user_id={$aUser.user_id}''); return false;&quot;&gt;{img theme=''module/chat.png'' class=''v_middle''} {phrase var=''profile.instant_chat''}&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt; \n            {/if}</code></pre>\n\nAnd replace it with:\n\n<pre><code>{if isset($aUser.is_online) &amp;&amp; $aUser.is_online &amp;&amp; Phpfox::isModule(''im'') &amp;&amp; Phpfox::getParam(''im.enable_im_in_footer_bar'') &amp;&amp; $aUser.is_friend == 1}\n            &lt;li&gt; \n            &lt;a href=&quot;javascript:void(0);&quot; onclick=&quot;jqcc.cometchat.chatWith(''{$aUser.user_id}'');&quot;&gt;{img theme=''module/chat.png'' class=''v_middle''} {phrase var=''profile.instant_chat''}&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;    {/if} </pre></code>', 'How do I add a "chat with me" link in the profile page?', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'how-do-i-add-a-chat-with-me-link-in-profile-page', '', '', '2012-04-21 12:24:49', '2012-04-21 06:54:49', '', 0, 'http://www.cometchat.com/answers/?p=68', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(72, 1, '2011-05-14 15:24:14', '2011-05-14 09:54:14', ' Languages section allows you to manage the language of the CometChat bar and plugins. Languages can be created and edited in minutes without any manual editing of files\n\n![Languages]\n(http://v6.cometchat.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2012/05/Languages.png)', 'Language', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'language', '', '', '2011-05-14 15:24:14', '2011-05-14 09:54:14', '', 4441, 'http://www.cometchat.com/documentation/?page_id=72', 37, 'page', '', 0),
(74, 1, '2012-04-21 12:35:17', '2012-04-21 07:05:17', 'Thank you for purchasing CometChat! 2checkout usually takes a couple of hours to pass every purchase through a fraud review check. Although you would have received a receipt from 2checkout immediately, we process orders as soon as this check is completed. We request you to wait a few hours.\n\nIf you do not hear from us, please <a href="/contact">create a support ticket</a> and we will be happy to assist you.', 'I have received a 2checkout receipt. But where is my download?', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'i-have-received-a-2checkout-receipt-but-where-is-my-download', '', '', '2012-04-21 12:35:17', '2012-04-21 07:05:17', '', 0, 'http://www.cometchat.com/answers/?p=74', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(77, 1, '2012-04-22 09:27:43', '2012-04-22 03:57:43', 'If you are using a new template or have updated your site software, CometChat may stop appearing on your site. Simply add the following code to your site template:\n\n<pre><code>&lt;link type=&quot;text/css&quot; href=&quot;/cometchat/cometchatcss.php&quot; rel=&quot;stylesheet&quot; charset=&quot;utf-8&quot;&gt;\n&lt;script type=&quot;text/javascript&quot; src=&quot;/cometchat/cometchatjs.php&quot; charset=&quot;utf-8&quot;&gt;&lt;/script&gt;</code></pre>', 'I need to insert the CometChat HTML code into my template again', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'i-need-to-insert-the-cometchat-html-code-into-my-template-again', '', '', '2012-04-22 09:27:43', '2012-04-22 03:57:43', '', 0, 'http://www.cometchat.com/answers/?p=77', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(78, 1, '2011-05-14 15:32:36', '2011-05-14 10:02:36', 'The *Settings* section in the *CometChat Administration Panel* enables you to tweak hundreds of features. If you are afraid that you will break the functionality, we strongly suggest you create a backup of *cometchat/config.php* file.\n\n![Settings]\n(http://v6.cometchat.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2012/04/settings.png)', 'Settings', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'settings', '', '', '2011-05-14 15:32:36', '2011-05-14 10:02:36', '', 4441, 'http://www.cometchat.com/documentation/?page_id=78', 118, 'page', '', 0),
(80, 1, '2011-05-14 15:39:20', '2011-05-14 10:09:20', '# Login to Administration Panel\n\n1. Point your browser to your CometChat Admin Panel\n2. Login and visit the settings page\n\n# Resizing the CometChat bar\n\nThe *Bar layout* can be set to the following:\n\n1. *Fluid* - The bar will be resized dynamically as the browser window is resized\n2. *Fixed* - The bar width will remain fixed irrespective of the size of the browser window\n\nWe highly recommend that you do not set the *width of the bar in pixels* is set to *960* or higher in case of *Fixed* bar layout.\n\n# Positioning the CometChat bar\n\nThe bar can be docked either on the left, center or right horizontally. Vertically, the position is always fixed to the bottom of the browser window.\n\nThe bar can be aligned only when the *Bar layout* is fixed. Edit the drop down *If set to fixed, enter alignment of the bar* as per your requirements.\n\n*Padding of bar* allows you to add spacing between the bar and the ends of the horizontal ends of the browser window.', 'Positioning and resizing the bar', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'positioning-and-resizing-the-bar', '', '', '2011-05-14 15:39:20', '2011-05-14 10:09:20', '', 465, 'http://www.cometchat.com/documentation/?page_id=80', 4, 'page', '', 0),
(83, 1, '2011-05-14 15:43:48', '2011-05-14 10:13:48', '# Login to Administration Panel\n\n1. Point your browser to your CometChat Admin Panel\n2. Login and visit the settings page\n\n# Activation\n\nThe lite version of CometChat can be activated by setting the *Switch on light-weight chat?* to *Yes* and clicking on the *Update Settings* button at the bottom of the page.\n\n# Advantages\n\n1. Light weight means faster loading times\n2. Facebook-like chat\n3. Unobtrusive and minimalistic\n\n# Disadvantages\n\n1. Does not allow use of *Modules* directly on the bar (they can be embedded in your page)\n2. Multiple chat boxes not fitting within the browser window will not add scroll arrows', 'Using Lite Version', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'using-lite-version', '', '', '2011-05-14 15:43:48', '2011-05-14 10:13:48', '', 465, 'http://www.cometchat.com/documentation/?page_id=83', 9, 'page', '', 0),
(85, 1, '2012-04-22 10:31:06', '2012-04-22 05:01:06', 'The most common reason for CometChat to disappear from your site is when you update your base software or change the site template. \n\nSimply add the following code to your site template after the <strong>&lt;head&gt;</strong> tag:\n\n<pre><code>&lt;link type=&quot;text/css&quot; href=&quot;/cometchat/cometchatcss.php&quot; rel=&quot;stylesheet&quot; charset=&quot;utf-8&quot;&gt;\n&lt;script type=&quot;text/javascript&quot; src=&quot;/cometchat/cometchatjs.php&quot; charset=&quot;utf-8&quot;&gt;&lt;/script&gt;</code></pre>', 'CometChat disappeared from my site', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'cometchat-disappeared-from-my-site', '', '', '2012-04-22 10:31:06', '2012-04-22 05:01:06', '', 0, 'http://www.cometchat.com/answers/?p=85', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(86, 1, '2011-05-14 16:11:42', '2011-05-14 10:41:42', '# Quick steps\n\n1. Disable chat history plugin and do not use logs option in admin panel\n2. Run http://www.yoursite.com/cometchat/cron.php periodically (every 3 hours)\n3. Show CometChat only for logged in users (i.e. hide bar for non-logged in users)\n4. Set CometChat to show only online friends/users in *Who''s Online* list\n5. Move the CometChat HTML code from just after `` to just before ``\n6. If you are using standalone integration, make sure that your mySQL queries are optimized\n\n# Alternatives\n\nIf your server is unable to handle the load, we suggest you subscribe to our [CometService](http://www.cometchat.com/cometservice). We also provide alternative transports- Self-hosted APE server, PusherApp and BeaconPush which can be used instead of CometService.\n', 'Optimizing Performance', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'optimizing-performance', '', '', '2011-05-14 16:11:42', '2011-05-14 10:41:42', '', 0, 'http://www.cometchat.com/documentation/?page_id=86', 93, 'page', '', 0),
(88, 1, '2012-04-23 11:36:56', '2012-04-23 06:06:56', 'Adobe Flash embeds do not follow standard <strong>z-index</strong> visibility rules. You will need to set the <strong>wmode</strong> parameter to <strong>transparent</strong> to make CometChat appear in front of Flash objects/advertisements.\n\nFor example, look at the wmode parameters in this sample YouTube code:\n\n<pre><code>&lt;object width=''425'' height=''344''&gt; \n    &lt;param name=''movie'' value=''http://www.youtube.com/v/Ahg6qcgoay4''&gt; \n    &lt;param name=''type'' value=''application/x-shockwave-flash''&gt; \n    &lt;param name=''allowfullscreen'' value=''true''&gt; \n    &lt;param name=''allowscriptaccess'' value=''always''&gt; \n    &lt;param name=&quot;wmode&quot; value=&quot;transparent&quot; /&gt;\n    &lt;embed width=''425'' height=''344''\n            src=''http://www.youtube.com/v/Ahg6qcgoay4''\n            type=''application/x-shockwave-flash''\n            allowfullscreen=''true''\n            allowscriptaccess=''always''\n            wmode=&quot;transparent&quot;\n    &gt;&lt;/embed&gt; \n    &lt;/object&gt;</code></pre>\n\nFor more information, refer to the Adobe article on <a href="http://helpx.adobe.com/flash/kb/transparent-background-swf-file.html" target="_blank">Transparent background in a SWF file</a>.', 'CometChat appears behind Flash objects/ads. Help!', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'cometchat-appears-behind-flash-objects', '', '', '2012-04-23 11:36:56', '2012-04-23 06:06:56', '', 0, 'http://www.cometchat.com/answers/?p=88', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(99, 1, '2012-05-14 15:18:47', '2012-05-14 09:48:47', 'To add a new smiley/emoticon, follow the steps listed below:\n\n1. You need to add the smiley image of your choice in the <strong>/cometchat/images/smileys</strong> directory.\n\n2. Then add its corresponding <strong>key-value pair</strong> to <strong>$smileys array</strong> in <strong>/cometchat/config.php</strong>.\n\nFor example, if you want to associate the new smiley image <strong>smiley_new.png</strong> with <strong>":)"</strong>, then add   <strong>'':)''=&gt;''smiley_new.png''</strong> as shown in the image below.\n\n<img src="http://v6.cometchat.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2012/05/smiley_new.png" alt="smiley_new" />', 'How can I add a new smiley/emoticon?', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'how-can-i-add-a-new-smiley', '', '', '2012-05-14 15:18:47', '2012-05-14 09:48:47', '', 0, 'http://www.cometchat.com/answers/?p=99', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(103, 1, '2011-10-11 15:06:41', '2011-10-11 09:36:41', '', 'CometChat v4 with Facebook/Gtalk chat', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', 'cometchat_4-0-0', '', '', '2011-10-11 15:06:41', '2011-10-11 09:36:41', '', 2005, 'http://v6.cometchat.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2011/10/cometchat_4.0.0.jpg', 0, 'attachment', 'image/jpeg', 0),
(105, 1, '2011-05-14 16:26:59', '2011-05-14 10:56:59', 'CometService offloads 95% of work to our servers and reduces message delivery time.\n\nCometService can be activated directly from the CometChat Administration Panel.\n\nTo use CometService, you need to perform two easy steps.		\n\n#Obtaining Keys		\n		\n1. Point your browser to [http://www.cometchat.com/cometservice](http://www.cometchat.com/cometservice) and select a plan of your choice.	\n\n2. After subscribing, you will receive an automated email from us.	\n\n3. Login to CometChat.com and visit [http://www.cometchat.com/my/cometservice](http://www.cometchat.com/my/cometservice)	\n\n4. Copy the keys from the page.		\n\n#Adding the Keys	\n\n1. Login to *CometChat Administration Panel*		\n\n2. Select *Settings* -&gt; *CometService*		\n\n3. Enter the keys and set *Use CometService* to *Yes*	\n\n![CometService](http://v6.cometchat.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/cometservice.png)', 'Using CometService', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'using-cometservice', '', '', '2011-05-14 16:26:59', '2011-05-14 10:56:59', '', 44, 'http://www.cometchat.com/documentation/?page_id=105', 72, 'page', '', 0),
(106, 1, '2012-05-10 16:14:39', '2012-05-10 10:44:39', 'This is usually caused due to restriction on executing <strong>index.php files</strong> by the code in <strong>.htaccess</strong> of your server. As a result <strong>index.php files</strong> inside the /cometchat directory are not accessible.\n\nTo fix this, <strong>add exception</strong> to <strong>execute</strong> all the <strong>index.php files</strong> inside the /cometchat directory and its sub-directories on your server.', 'None of the modules and plugins of CometChat load on my site. How do I fix this?', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'none-of-the-modules-and-plugins-of-cometchat-load-on-my-site-how-do-i-fix-this', '', '', '2012-05-10 16:14:39', '2012-05-10 10:44:39', '', 0, 'http://www.cometchat.com/answers/?p=106', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(107, 1, '2011-05-14 16:30:45', '2011-05-14 11:00:45', '&gt; You need to purchase the Pusher transport before proceeding with the steps below. To purchase, please create a support ticket.\n\n# Obtaining the keys\n\nVisit [http://www.pusher.com](http://www.pusher.com) and register on the site. Create a new app and get the relevant keys.\n\n# Adding the keys\n\n1. Upload the *pusher* folder to the *cometchat/transports* folder\n2. Edit *cometchat/transports/pusher/config.php*\n3. Edit *cometchat/config.php* and find *COMET*.\n\nModify the code to the following:\n\n	define(''USE_COMET'',''1'');\n	define(''COMET_HISTORY_LIMIT'',''100'');\n	define(''KEY_A'',''RANDOMSTRING1'');\n	define(''KEY_B'',''RANDOMSTRING2'');\n	define(''KEY_C'',''RANDOMSTRING3'');\n	define(''SAVE_LOGS'',''0'');\n	\n	/* COMET END */\n	\n	define(''TRANSPORT'',''pusher'');', 'Using PusherApp', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'using-pusherapp', '', '', '2011-05-14 16:30:45', '2011-05-14 11:00:45', '', 44, 'http://www.cometchat.com/documentation/?page_id=107', 74, 'page', '', 0),
(108, 1, '2012-06-01 16:13:47', '2012-06-01 10:43:47', 'To add an animated GIF smiley, follow the steps listed below:\n\n1. You need to add the smiley image of your choice in the <strong>/cometchat/images/smileys directory</strong>.\n\n2. Then add its corresponding <strong>key-value pair</strong> to <strong>$smileys array</strong> in <strong>/cometchat/config.php</strong>.\n\nFor example, if you want to associate the new smiley image <strong>smile.gif</strong> with <strong>":)"</strong>, then add   <strong>'':)''=&gt;''smile.gif''</strong> as shown in the image below.\n\n<img src="http://v6.cometchat.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2012/05/smiley_new1.png" alt="smiley_new1" />\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n', 'How can I add an animated GIF smiley?', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'how-can-i-add-an-animated-gif-smiley', '', '', '2012-06-01 16:13:47', '2012-06-01 10:43:47', '', 0, 'http://www.cometchat.com/answers/?p=108', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(110, 1, '2011-05-14 16:31:34', '2011-05-14 11:01:34', '&gt; You need to purchase the BeaconPush transport before proceeding with the steps below. To purchase, please create a support ticket.\n\n# Obtaining the keys\n\nVisit [http://www.beaconpush.com](http://www.beaconpush.com) and register on the site. Note the relevant keys.\n\n# Adding the keys\n\n1. Upload the *beaconpush* folder to the *cometchat/transports* folder\n2. Edit *cometchat/transports/beaconpush/config.php*\n3. Edit *cometchat/config.php* and find *COMET*.\n\nModify the code to the following:\n\n	define(''USE_COMET'',''1'');\n	define(''COMET_HISTORY_LIMIT'',''100'');\n	define(''KEY_A'',''RANDOMSTRING1'');\n	define(''KEY_B'',''RANDOMSTRING2'');\n	define(''KEY_C'',''RANDOMSTRING3'');\n	define(''SAVE_LOGS'',''0'');\n	\n	/* COMET END */\n	\n	define(''TRANSPORT'',''beaconpush'');', 'Using BeaconPush', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'using-beaconpush', '', '', '2011-05-14 16:31:34', '2011-05-14 11:01:34', '', 44, 'http://www.cometchat.com/documentation/?page_id=110', 74, 'page', '', 0),
(111, 1, '2012-06-01 15:55:33', '2012-06-01 10:25:33', 'To retain the original size of the smileys, you need to <strong>remove</strong> the <strong>height</strong> and <strong>width</strong> attribute from the following code in <strong>cometchat/cometchat_shared.php</strong>:\n\n<pre><code>$text = str_ireplace(str_replace(''&amp;'',''&amp;'',htmlspecialchars($pattern, ENT_NOQUOTES)).'' '',''&lt;img class="cometchat_smiley" height="16" width="16" src="''.BASE_URL.''images/smileys/''.$result.''" title="''.$title.''"&gt; '',$text.'' '');</pre></code>\n\nReplace $text to: \n\n<pre><code>$text = str_ireplace(str_replace(''&amp;'',''&amp;'',htmlspecialchars($pattern, ENT_NOQUOTES)).'' '',''&lt;img class="cometchat_smiley" src="''.BASE_URL.''images/smileys/''.$result.''"&gt; '',$text.'' '');</pre></code>\n\nAnd to increase the size of the smileys, simply <strong>modify</strong> the <strong>height</strong> and <strong>width</strong> attribute of the image.\nFor example if you want to set the size of the image to 30x30, you need to set the height and width attribute as shown below:\n\n<pre><code>$text = str_ireplace(str_replace(''&amp;'',''&amp;'',htmlspecialchars($pattern, ENT_NOQUOTES)).'' '',''&lt;img class="cometchat_smiley" height="30" width="30" src="''.BASE_URL.''images/smileys/''.$result.''" title="''.$title.''"&gt; '',$text.'' '');</code></pre>', 'How do I retain the original size of the smileys/emoticons or increase their size?', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'how-do-i-retain-the-original-size-of-the-smileysemoticons-or-increase-their-size', '', '', '2012-06-01 15:55:33', '2012-06-01 10:25:33', '', 0, 'http://www.cometchat.com/answers/?p=111', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(112, 1, '2011-05-14 16:32:51', '2011-05-14 11:02:51', '&gt; You need to purchase the APE server transport before proceeding with the steps below. To purchase, please create a support ticket.\n\n# Installation of APE Server\n\n1. Visit [http://www.ape-project.org](http://www.ape-project.org) and [download APE Server](http://www.ape-project.org/download/)\n2. [Install APE Server](http://www.ape-project.org/wiki/index.php/Setup) on any standard VPS or dedicated server\n\n&gt; We do not provide support for installation and/or maintenance of APE Server. Please use any third-party service to manage your APE server installation. We recommend APE Server only for users who wish to handle all their communication internally. For cheaper alternatives of CometService, we suggest you use BeaconPush or PusherApp.\n\n# Configuring CometChat\n\n1. Upload the *ape* folder to the *cometchat/transports* folder\n2. Edit *cometchat/transports/ape/config.php*\n3. Edit *cometchat/config.php* and find *COMET*.\n\nModify the code to the following:\n\n    define(''USE_COMET'',''1'');\n    define(''COMET_HISTORY_LIMIT'',''100'');\n    define(''KEY_A'',''RANDOMSTRING1'');\n    define(''KEY_B'',''RANDOMSTRING2'');\n    define(''KEY_C'',''RANDOMSTRING3'');\n    define(''SAVE_LOGS'',''0'');\n	\n    /* COMET END */\n	\n    define(''TRANSPORT'',''ape'');', 'Using APE Server', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'using-ape-server', '', '', '2011-05-14 16:32:51', '2011-05-14 11:02:51', '', 44, 'http://www.cometchat.com/documentation/?page_id=112', 74, 'page', '', 0);
INSERT INTO `ccwp_posts` (`ID`, `post_author`, `post_date`, `post_date_gmt`, `post_content`, `post_title`, `post_excerpt`, `post_status`, `comment_status`, `ping_status`, `post_password`, `post_name`, `to_ping`, `pinged`, `post_modified`, `post_modified_gmt`, `post_content_filtered`, `post_parent`, `guid`, `menu_order`, `post_type`, `post_mime_type`, `comment_count`) VALUES
(116, 1, '2012-05-10 16:17:04', '2012-05-10 10:47:04', 'Please add the following CometChat footer code in your Vbulletin admincp -&gt; styles -&gt; templates -&gt; search styles -&gt;search for ''head'' -&gt; default theme(your site''s theme) -&gt; header  \n\nNow find the CometChat HTML code and replace it with the following:\n \n<pre><code>&lt;vb:if condition=&quot;is_member_of($bbuserinfo, 6,7,9,10,16)&quot;&gt;\n&lt;link type=&quot;text/css&quot; href=&quot;/cometchat/cometchatcss.php&quot; rel=&quot;stylesheet&quot; charset=&quot;utf-8&quot;&gt;\n&lt;script type=&quot;text/javascript&quot; src=&quot;/cometchat/cometchatjs.php&quot; charset=&quot;utf-8&quot;&gt;&lt;/script&gt;\n&lt;/vb:if&gt;</code></pre>\n\n \nIn the above code, you will have to replace <strong>6,7,9,10,16</strong> as per your requirements. \n\nFor example, if you want to allow only <strong>usergroups 1 </strong>and <strong>2</strong> with access, then your code will be:\n \n<pre><code>&lt;vb:if condition=&quot;is_member_of($bbuserinfo, 1,2)&quot;&gt;\n&lt;link type=&quot;text/css&quot; href=&quot;/cometchat/cometchatcss.php&quot; rel=&quot;stylesheet&quot; charset=&quot;utf-8&quot;&gt;\n&lt;script type=&quot;text/javascript&quot; src=&quot;/cometchat/cometchatjs.php&quot; charset=&quot;utf-8&quot;&gt;&lt;/script&gt;\n&lt;/vb:if&gt;</code></pre>\n\n\nAlso, make sure your path to <strong>CometChat JS/CSS files</strong> is correct in the above code.\n                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                               ', 'How to show CometChat to certain usergroups only?', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'how-to-show-cometchat-to-certain-usergroups-only', '', '', '2012-05-10 16:17:04', '2012-05-10 10:47:04', '', 0, 'http://www.cometchat.com/answers/?p=116', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(121, 1, '2011-11-11 15:09:56', '2011-11-11 09:39:56', 'Thank you for your tremendous response to our CometChat v4 release! We have had the chance to tweak many of our modules over the last couple of weeks.\n\n<h2>Highlights</h2>\n\n<strong>High definition video chat</strong>\n\nThe launch of <a href="http://www.adobe.com/products/flashplayer/features._sl_id-contentfilter_sl_featuredisplaytypes_sl_new.html" title="Adobe Flash Player 11 New Features" target="_blank">Adobe Flash Player 11</a> brings in the ability to encode at H.264 (standard codec for high-def videos like Blu-ray). Our voice/video chat plugin has been automatically updated for all our customers. You and your users only have to <a href="http://get.adobe.com/flashplayer/" title="Adobe Flash Player 11" target="_blank">get the latest version</a> of Adobe Flash Player to be able to video chat in HD. We have also added an option for peer-to-peer chat in the latest update.\n\n<img src="http://v6.cometchat.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2011/11/videochat.jpg" style="border:1px solid #ccc">\n\n<strong>Facebook/Gtalk friends chat</strong>\n\nOur Facebook/Gtalk chat has been updated with miscellaneous tweaks and fixes. We have upgraded our servers as well to ensure smooth scaling. Caching has now been enabled so avatar images will load instantly for subsequent calls.\n\n<strong>Single player games</strong>\n\nWe have tied up with a new partner to provide you with high quality single player games.\n\n<img src="http://v6.cometchat.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2011/11/singleplayergames.jpg" style="border:1px solid #ccc">\n\n<strong>New real-time translate module</strong>\n\nOur old real-time translate module which used Google''s free translate API will cease to function from December 1st. This is because of <a href="http://googlecode.blogspot.com/2011/05/spring-cleaning-for-some-of-our-apis.html" target="_blank">Google''s decision</a> to discontinue their free translate API service. \n\nWe have updated the module well in advance so that the transition phase is smooth. You can now use either Google''s paid translate API or Microsoft''s free translate API. Learn <a href="http://www.cometchat.com/documentation/admin/modules/real-time-translate">how to configure the new real-time translate module</a>.\n\n<strong>New writeboard plugin</strong>\n\nThe writeboard plugin has been updated with a slicker interface. We are now hosting this service on our servers for better performance.\n\n<img src="http://v6.cometchat.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2011/11/writeboard2.jpg" style="border:1px solid #ccc">\n\n<strong>Aggressive caching</strong>\n\nThe CometChat base code has been slightly tweaked for caching so the CometChat core files are downloaded only once. The advantages are two-fold: your site loads considerably faster and bandwidth usage is much lower.\n\n<h2>Like what you see?</h2>\n\n<a href="http://www.cometchat.com/my">Upgrade to a higher edition</a> by simply paying the difference, <a href="http://www.cometchat.com/buy">purchase CometChat</a> or <a href="http://www.cometchat.com/contact">ask us a question</a>.\n\nWould you like to see a new feature in the next release? <a href="http://cometchat.uservoice.com" target="_blank">Add your suggestion!</a>', 'HD video chat, new games and a lot more', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'hd-video-chat-new-games-and-a-lot-more', '', '', '2011-11-11 15:09:56', '2011-11-11 09:39:56', '', 0, 'http://www.cometchat.com/blog/?p=121', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(124, 1, '2011-05-14 20:54:11', '2011-05-14 15:24:11', 'Permanent Chatrooms can only be added via the Administration Panel. User created chatrooms are auto-deleted after 10 minutes of non-activity.		\n\n![list of chatrooms](http://v6.cometchat.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/List+of+Chatrooms.png)\n\nTo create a Chatroom, simply visit ***CometChat Administration Panel -&gt; chatrooms -&gt; Add new chatroom***\n\nYou can either create a public chatroom or password protected chatroom.	\n\n#Add New Chatrooms 		\n\n* To create a Public room:		\n\n1. Name the chatroom and select Type as ***Public room*** from the drop down box.\n2. Click on the ***Add Chatroom*** button to create the chatroom.\n\n![Chatrooms](http://v6.cometchat.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/chatrooms.png)		\n\n* To create a Password protected room:	\n\n1. Name the chatroom and select Type as *Password protected room* from the drop down box.\n2. Enter the password and click on the *Add Chatroom* button to create the chatroom.\n\n![password protected room](http://v6.cometchat.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/password+protected+room.png)		\n\n#Manage Modearators\nAdmins can depute moderation powers to their users. 		\nThese moderators can supervise any of the rooms (i.e. public and password protected rooms). They also have the power to kick or ban any user from any chatrooms.		\n				\nWith Manage moderators option the owner can administer/manage these moderators. 		\n\n![manage+moderators](http://v6.cometchat.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/manage+moderators.png)		\n\nTo view the number of available chatrooms, click on the *Chatrooms* option as shown in the image below:\n\n![remove embed](http://v6.cometchat.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/remove-embed.png)		\n\nClick on ![link](http://v6.cometchat.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/link1.png) button to directly go to a particular chatroom.		\n\nClick on ![embed](http://v6.cometchat.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/embed.png) button to generate embed code for a chatroom. Copy this code and paste it on your site to make the chatroom permanently visible on the site.		\n\nClick on ![remove](http://v6.cometchat.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/remove1.png) button to remove a particular chatroom.', 'Chatrooms', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'chatrooms', '', '', '2011-05-14 20:54:11', '2011-05-14 15:24:11', '', 4441, 'http://www.cometchat.com/documentation/?page_id=124', 33, 'page', '', 0),
