(301, 1, '2011-05-15 16:56:37', '2011-05-15 11:26:37', 'sendChatroomMessage() allows you to dynamically send messages to a particular chatroom.\n\n# The API\n\n	sendChatroomMessage($chatroomID,$message);\n	\n# Sample Code\n\nYou can find out the chatroom ID from *CometChat Administration Panel* -&gt; *Chatrooms*. A sample use would be to post a message on behalf of the user in a chatroom.\n		\n	include_once (cometchat/cometchat_init.php);\n	sendChatroomMessage (''1'',"I love this site! I have already donated, have you?");', 'sendChatroomMessage()', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'sendchatroommessage', '', '', '2011-05-15 16:56:37', '2011-05-15 11:26:37', '', 294, 'http://www.cometchat.com/documentation/?page_id=301', 66, 'page', '', 0),
(302, 1, '2012-05-10 15:57:42', '2012-05-10 10:27:42', 'To make the CometChat bar visible on your site, you need to clear dolphin cache in <strong>/cache</strong> and <strong>/cache_public directories</strong>.', 'CometChat is not visible after adding the HTML code to the footer', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'cometchat-is-not-visible-after-adding-the-html-code-to-the-footer', '', '', '2012-05-10 15:57:42', '2012-05-10 10:27:42', '', 0, 'http://www.cometchat.com/answers/?p=302', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(303, 1, '2011-05-15 16:59:44', '2011-05-15 11:29:44', 'sanitize() function allows you to clean up user input and process it as per CometChat''s settings.\n\n# The API\n\nThe function will return the new value after it has been sanitized and processed. During processing hyperlinks, banned words and smileys maybe added depending on your configuration.\n\n	sanitize($message);\n	\nIf you wish to only clean the input, use `sanitize_core($message)`', 'sanitize()', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'sanitize', '', '', '2011-05-15 16:59:44', '2011-05-15 11:29:44', '', 294, 'http://www.cometchat.com/documentation/?page_id=303', 74, 'page', '', 0),
(305, 1, '2011-05-15 17:02:58', '2011-05-15 11:32:58', 'sendMessageTo() allows you to dynamically send message (one-way) to a particular user. This message will not appear in the senders chat box screen.\n\n# The API\n\n	sendMessageTo($to,$message);\n	\n# Sample Code\n\nThis function is ideally used in plugins to inform the user of an activity. The sender will not receive the same message.\n		\n	include_once (cometchat/cometchat_init.php);\n	sendMessageTo($toID,"Would you like to have a Pizza?");\n', 'sendMessageTo', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'sendmessageto', '', '', '2011-05-15 17:02:58', '2011-05-15 11:32:58', '', 294, 'http://www.cometchat.com/documentation/?page_id=305', 67, 'page', '', 0),
(306, 1, '2012-05-09 16:14:03', '2012-05-09 10:44:03', '', 'rename_module_to', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', 'rename_module_to', '', '', '2012-05-09 16:14:03', '2012-05-09 10:44:03', '', 279, 'http://v6.cometchat.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2012/05/rename_module_to.jpg', 0, 'attachment', 'image/jpeg', 0),
(307, 1, '2011-05-15 17:05:44', '2011-05-15 11:35:44', 'sendSelfMessage() allows you to dynamically send message (one-way) from a particular user. This message will only appear in the senders chat box screen.\n\n# The API\n\nThe $to is the user''s ID of the chat box and not the user to whom this message is being sent.\n\n	sendSelfMessage($to,$message);\n	\n# Sample Code\n\nThis function is ideally used in plugins to inform the user of activity completion. The sender will only receive the same message.\n		\n	include_once (cometchat/cometchat_init.php);\n	sendSelfMessage($toID,"has successfully sent Pizza request.");\n', 'sendSelfMessage()', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'sendselfmessage', '', '', '2011-05-15 17:05:44', '2011-05-15 11:35:44', '', 294, 'http://www.cometchat.com/documentation/?page_id=307', 72, 'page', '', 0),
(311, 1, '2012-07-18 16:45:07', '2012-07-18 11:15:07', 'As you may be aware, our existing whiteboard and screen sharing plugins, made use Adobe LCCS. Adobe has decided to discontinue this service without prior intimation. When we first heard about this from Adobe, we immediately began work to create new plugins which <strong>do not</strong> rely on this service. \n\nAlong the way, we had a chance to add new features as well!\n\n<h2>Screen sharing with screen control</h2>\n\nThe new screen sharing plugin allows your users to control the screen remotely! Not only can your users view each other''s screens, they can also control them.\n\n<img src="http://v6.cometchat.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2012/06/ScreenshareFrontend3.png" alt="" title="Screen sharing" width="405" height="103" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-315" />\n\n<img src="http://v6.cometchat.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2012/06/screenshareFrontend6.png" alt="" title="Screen viewing with control" width="642" height="509" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-317" />\n\n<h2>Whiteboard</h2>\n\nThe new whiteboard plugin has tons of new options and a cleaner layout which blends smoothly into our existing look and feel. \n\n<img src="http://v6.cometchat.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2012/06/whiteboardfront-end3.png" alt="" title="Whiteboard" width="643" height="514" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-319" />\n\n<h2>Requirements</h2>\n\nIf you would like to use the screen sharing, you will need RED5 server (open-source). The software can either be hosted on your own server or you can use a third-party host. You can learn more by reading up our <a href="http://www.cometchat.com/documentation/admin/plugins/screensharing-plugin">configuration guide for screen sharing</a>.\n\nIf you would like to use whiteboard plugin, you will need either RED5 (open-source) or Adobe FMS server (commercial). Both software can either be hosted on your own server or you can use a third-party host. You can learn more by reading up our <a href="http://www.cometchat.com/documentation/admin/plugins/whiteboard-plugin">configuration guide for whiteboard</a>.\n\nFeel free to <a href="http://www.cometchat.com/contact">email us</a> if you have any questions.', 'New Whiteboard and Screen sharing with screen control!', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'new-whiteboard-and-screen-sharing-with-screen-control', '', '', '2012-07-18 16:45:07', '2012-07-18 11:15:07', '', 0, 'http://www.cometchat.com/blog/?p=311', 0, 'post', '', 0),
