(625, 1, '2013-04-02 12:00:13', '2013-04-02 06:30:13', '<a href="http://www.youtube.com/cometchattv" title="CometChatTV" target="_blank"><img src="http://v6.cometchat.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2012/06/cometchattv.jpg" alt="" title="Youtube.com/CometChatTV" width="640" height="150" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-284" /></a>\n\nWe have added new tour video of our CometChat Mobile App (for iOS &amp; Android) at <a href="http://www.youtube.com/cometchattv" title="CometChatTV" target="_blank"><strong>CometChatTV</strong></a>.\n\n\n\n<a href="https://itunes.apple.com/ca/app/cometchat/id594110077" target="_blank"><img style="border:0" src="http://v6.cometchat.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2013/02/applestore.png" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-536" /></a> &nbsp; &nbsp; <a href="https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.inscripts.cometchat" target="_blank"><img style="border:0" src="http://v6.cometchat.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2013/02/googleplay.png" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-536" /></a>\n\n<strong>Need custom branding?</strong>\n\n<a href="http://www.cometchat.com/my">Purchase white-labelled version of our mobile apps</a> for just $399 (includes both iOS &amp; Android). Our white-labelled apps are customized specifically for your site. So your logo, your app name, your colors and no URL bar (in the login page).\n\nView all our videos at our new <a href="http://www.youtube.com/user/cometchattv" title="CometChatTV" target="_blank">Youtube Channel</a> or subscribe to stay informed.\n\n<a href="//www.youtube.com/subscription_center?add_user_id=Wu7LtG16A9ZgcyBpNMCX0Q&amp;feature=creators_cornier-//s.ytimg.com/yt/img/creators_corner/Subscribe_to_my_videos/YT_Subscribe_160x27_red.png"><img src="//s.ytimg.com/yt/img/creators_corner/Subscribe_to_my_videos/YT_Subscribe_160x27_red.png" style="border:0px" alt="Subscribe to me on YouTube" /></a>', 'CometChat Mobile Tour', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'cometchat-mobile-tour', '', '', '2013-04-02 12:00:13', '2013-04-02 06:30:13', '', 0, 'http://www.cometchat.com/blog/?p=625', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(630, 1, '2012-04-17 19:45:15', '2012-04-17 14:15:15', 'Extensions add additional functionality to CometChat.\n\nThe center section displays the *live extensions*. On the right hand side, the *Available Extensions* shows the extensions that you can integrate instantly just by clicking on the *add* button.\n\n![Extensions](http://v6.cometchat.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/liveextensions.png)		', 'Extensions', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'extensions', '', '', '2012-04-17 19:45:15', '2012-04-17 14:15:15', '', 4441, 'http://www.cometchat.com/documentation/?page_id=630', 35, 'page', '', 0),
(634, 1, '2012-04-17 20:01:13', '2012-04-17 14:31:13', '#Using your own Facebook Application\n\nIf your site already uses Facebook to allow users to login, then you can use the same Facebook Application when your users connect via CometChat to chat with their Facebook friends.\n\n#Configuring your Facebook Application		\n\n* Login to Facebook and go to your application in the developers section		\n\n* Note the *App ID* and *App Secret*		\n\n![Facebook app](http://v6.cometchat.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/facebook+app.png)		\n\n* Click on *Edit Settings* and update your *App Domain* to include *chatforyoursite.com*		\n\n* Then update *Mobile Web URL* to *http://chatforyoursite.com*		\n\n**Do not rename “chatforyoursite.com” to “chatforYOURACTUALSITENAME.com”. It is meant to be “chatforyoursite.com”, a domain that we own and use to enable Facebook chat**.	\n	\n![facebook+app+1](http://v6.cometchat.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/facebook+app+1.png)		\n\n* Click on the *Save Changes* button and wait 3-10 minutes for the changes to propagate.		\n\n#Configuring the extension	\n\n1. In the Extensions section, add the *Facebook/Gtalk/XMPP extension* to your *live extensions* and click on the *config* link besides the name.		\n		\n2. Enter the details you noted previously			\n\n3. Click on the *Update Settings* button and close the window\n\n![Facebook configuration](http://v6.cometchat.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/facebook+config.png)\n\n<blockquote>\n<p>If you do not want the user to see the Facebook permissions dialog when logging into chat, add the following parameters in your Facebook Connect settings: offline_access, xmpp_login</p>\n</blockquote>			\n	\n\n#Using your own Gtalk Application	\nSimilar to facebook appplication, if your site already uses google to allow users to login, then you can use the same google Application when your users connect via CometChat to chat with their Gtalk friends.	\n\n#Configuring your Gtalk Application\n\n* Login to Google and go to your application in the developers section ( for this point your browser to the following: *https://code.google.com/apis/console/*)		\n\n* Note the *Client ID* and *Client Secret*\n\n![Gtalk configuration](http://v6.cometchat.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/screenshot1.png)	\n\n* Click on Edit Settings and update your App Domain to include *chatforyoursite.com*		\n		\n* Set Authorized Redirect URL to: 	\n*http://j.chatforyoursite.com/gtalk.html*	\n*https://j.chatforyoursite.com/gtalk.html*	\n	\n* Then Set Authorized Javascript Origins to:	\n*http://j.chatforyoursite.com*  	\n*https://j.chatforyoursite.com*\n\n![Google Settings](http://v6.cometchat.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/google_editsettings.png)		\n\n* Click on the Save Changes button and wait 3-10 minutes for the changes to propagate.		\n\n#Configuring the extension	\n\n1. In the Extensions section, add the *Facebook/Gtalk/XMPP extension* to your *live extensions* and click on the *config* link besides the name.	\n		\n2. Enter the details you noted previously			\n\n3. Click on the *Update Settings* button and close the window\n\n![Settings](http://v6.cometchat.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/fbgtalk+settings+-+Copy.png)', 'Facebook/Gtalk/XMPP Extension', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'facebook-gtalk-extension', '', '', '2012-04-17 20:01:13', '2012-04-17 14:31:13', '', 630, 'http://www.cometchat.com/documentation/?page_id=634', 0, 'page', '', 0),
