(726, 1, '2012-05-18 18:32:34', '2012-05-18 13:02:34', 'If you get ''Unable to connect to database'' error, refer to the solutions listed below:\n\n<strong>1. Re-download CometChat</strong>\n\nThe most common cause of this issue is an <strong>incorrectly downloaded integration file</strong>. If you are integrating CometChat with WordPress and you select BuddyPress from the drop-down menu before download, the installation will not work correctly.\n\n<strong>2. Incorrect Folder</strong>\n\nThe CometChat folder must be uploaded to the <strong>correct directory</strong>. Please make sure you upload it to the software <strong>root folder</strong>.\n\n<strong>3. Custom Site</strong>\n\nIf you are integrating CometChat with a <strong>custom site</strong>, you will have to manually edit <strong>integration.php</strong> and add the database details. Do not make this modification if you are using any ready-to-use integration like WordPress, vBulletin etc.', 'I get ''Unable to connect to database'' error when I try to add CometChat on my site.', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'i-get-unable-to-connect-to-database-error-when-i-try-to-add-cometchat-on-my-site', '', '', '2012-05-18 18:32:34', '2012-05-18 13:02:34', '', 0, 'http://www.cometchat.com/answers/?p=726', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(728, 1, '2012-06-01 16:21:37', '2012-06-01 10:51:37', 'If you are unable to find the &lt;HEAD&gt; tag in your site template, you will have to perform the following steps:\n\nYou need to manually edit <strong>libraries/joomla/document/html/renderer/head.php</strong>. Please backup this file before proceeding.\n\nFind the following comment on line 87:\n\n<pre>// Generate link declarations</pre>\n\nAdd the following code just before the comment:\n\n<pre><code>$strHtml .= ''&lt;link type="text/css" rel="stylesheet" media="all" href="/cometchat/cometchatcss.php" charset="utf-8" /&gt;&lt;script type="text/javascript" src="/cometchat/cometchatjs.php" charset="utf-8"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;'';\n</code></pre>\n\nSo the new code will look like:\n\n<pre><code>$strHtml .= ''&lt;link type="text/css" rel="stylesheet" media="all" href="/cometchat/cometchatcss.php" charset="utf-8" /&gt;&lt;script type="text/javascript" src="/cometchat/cometchatjs.php" charset="utf-8"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;'';\n\n// Generate link declarations\n</code></pre>\n\n<blockquote>$strHtml variable name may be different (e.g. $buffer) in different Joomla installations.</blockquote>\n\nSave your file and then you can continue with the rest of the installation.', 'I am unable to find HTML code in my Joomla site template.', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'i-am-unable-to-find-html-code-in-my-joomla-site-template', '', '', '2012-06-01 16:21:37', '2012-06-01 10:51:37', '', 0, 'http://www.cometchat.com/answers/?p=728', 0, 'post', '', 0),
