(786, 1, '2012-06-01 16:24:05', '2012-06-01 10:54:05', 'CometChat v3.0.9 and higher versions, provides full cross-domain support. You can run CometChat across <strong>multiple domains/sub-domains</strong> using this feature.\n\nAn ideal use of this feature is when you have CometChat installed at www.yoursite.com and also want to use it on abc.yoursite.com.\n\nTo use CometChat across multiple sub-domains, follow the steps listed below:\n\n	<li>\n<ol>\n\nEdit <strong>cometchat/config.php</strong> and set <strong>BASE_URL</strong> to the full path e.g. <strong>http://www.yoursite.com/cometchat/</strong>\n</ol>\n\n</li>\n\n\n	<li>\n<ol>\n\nThen set <strong>CROSS_DOMAIN</strong> to <strong>1</strong>\n</ol>\n\n</li>\n\n\n<img src="http://v6.cometchat.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2012/05/crossdomain1.png" alt="Crossdomain" />\n	<li>\n<ol>\n\nAdd the following code to the site template of your sub-domains (remember to include the full URL path).\n</ol>\n\n</li>\n\nAdd the code immediately after  tag:\n\n<pre><code>&lt;link type=&quot;text/css&quot; rel=&quot;stylesheet&quot; media=&quot;all&quot; href=&quot;http://www.yoursite.com/cometchat/cometchatcss.php&quot; /&gt; \n&lt;script type=&quot;text/javascript&quot; src=&quot;http://www.yoursite.com/cometchat/cometchatjs.php&quot; charset=&quot;utf-8&quot;&gt;&lt;/script&gt;</code></pre>\n\n<strong>Your users must be logged into your main site inorder to use CometChat in your sub-domains.</strong>\n\n\n\n<blockquote>Use of CometService or alternatives is strongly recommended when using CometChat in cross-domain environment.</blockquote>', 'How to use CometChat across multiple sub-domains?', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'how-to-use-cometchat-across-multiple-sub-domains', '', '', '2012-06-01 16:24:05', '2012-06-01 10:54:05', '', 0, 'http://www.cometchat.com/answers/?p=786', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(807, 1, '2012-05-24 19:24:55', '2012-05-24 13:54:55', 'Once you have installed CometChat on your site, there maybe certain static pages or other templates where you would like to show CometChat.\n\nA typical scenario is when you have both JomSocial and WordPress installed on your site. In this case, it is advisable to install CometChat for JomSocial. \n\nThen to add CometChat to your WordPress site, simply perform the following step:\n\nAdd the CometChat HTML code to the WordPress site template (or any other static HTML pages):\n\n<pre><code>\n&lt;link type=&quot;text/css&quot; rel=&quot;stylesheet&quot; media=&quot;all&quot; href=&quot;/cometchat/cometchatcss.php&quot; /&gt; \n&lt;script type=&quot;text/javascript&quot; src=&quot;/cometchat/cometchatjs.php&quot; charset=&quot;utf-8&quot;&gt;&lt;/script&gt;\n</code></pre>\n\nThat’s all! Whenever your user logs into JomSocial, they will be able to use CometChat in your WordPress portion of the site as well.', 'How can I have CometChat on all the pages of my website?', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'how-can-i-have-cometchat-on-all-the-pages-of-my-website', '', '', '2012-05-24 19:24:55', '2012-05-24 13:54:55', '', 0, 'http://www.cometchat.com/answers/?p=807', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(814, 1, '2012-05-18 14:34:45', '2012-05-18 09:04:45', 'You can easily generate iframe codes, remove an existing module, open a module in lightbox/pop ups or display the title for different modules in your website with the help of different options available in the center section.  \n\n![annotationsfinal]\n(http://v6.cometchat.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2012/05/annotationsfinal.png)\n\n# Show/Hide title of a module\n\nTo show the title of any module in the chat bar, click on the ***Show/Hide Title*** button of the respective Module.\n\n![Show module titles]\n(http://v6.cometchat.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2012/05/Show+module+titles.png)\n\nTo hide the titles of these modules, click on the same button.\n\n![Hide module title]\n(http://v6.cometchat.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2012/05/hide+modules+titles.png)\n\n# Open module in a light-box/popup\n\nTo open a module in a light box, click on the ***Light Box*** button.\nWith this feature, the selected module will appear as a *light box*. You can drag this light box anywhere on your screen. \n\n![Translate Conversation Lightbox]\n(http://v6.cometchat.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2012/05/Translate+Conversation+Lightbox.png)\n\nTo set the module as a *popup*, click on the same button.\n\n![Translate Conversation Popup]\n(http://v6.cometchat.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2012/05/Translate+Conversation+Popup.png)\n\n# Embed Module into your site\n\nClick on the ***Generate Embed Code*** button, next to the module that you would like to embed.\n\nFor example:-	\n\n* Click on the *Generate Embed Code* button of the **‘Games’** module.	 \n* A window pops out with the *iframe HTML code*.	\n* Copy the code and add to your site page.	\n\n ![embed link1]\n(http://v6.cometchat.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2012/05/embed+link1.png)\n\n* Now the Game Module will be visible on your site’s page.	\n\n![Embed game module]\n(http://v6.cometchat.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2012/05/abc.png)\n\n# Configure Module\n\nWith this option you can change the setting of any module.\n\nTo configure a module, click on the *Configure Module* button. A window pops out where you can change the settings of a module accordingly.\n\nFor example:-\n\n* To configure the **Chatrooms module**, click on the *Configure Module* button.	\n* Set the values for the chatroom settings	\n* Then click on the *Update Settings* button.\n\n![Modules - Settings]\n(http://v6.cometchat.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2012/04/chatroom+modules.png)\n\nSimilarly, configuration can be done for Games, Facebook Fan Page, Twitter and Translate Conversation modules.\n\n# Remove Module\n\nClick on the *Remove Module* button to remove a module from the chat bar', 'Configuring Modules', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'configuring-modules', '', '', '2012-05-18 14:34:45', '2012-05-18 09:04:45', '', 4625, 'http://www.cometchat.com/documentation/?page_id=814', 9, 'page', '', 0),
