(4290, 1, '2013-03-14 16:26:22', '2013-03-14 10:56:22', 'There are 3 different technologies with which you can achieve high quality broadcasting:\n\n1. CometChat Server\n2. RED5 or FMS (RTMP)\n3. FMS (RTMFP)', 'Audio Video Broadcast', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'audio-video-broadcast', '', '', '2013-03-14 16:26:22', '2013-03-14 10:56:22', '', 62, 'http://www.cometchat.com/documentation/?page_id=4290', 6, 'page', '', 0),
(4293, 1, '2013-03-14 16:29:54', '2013-03-14 10:59:54', ' Runs from our servers. No special software is required. Use of this technology/option is absolutely free and recommended.\n\nTo use this server select CometChat server from the *Technology Dropdown* box. 	\n\nSet the *Video width* and *height* accordingly and click on the *Update Settings* button.\n\n![broadcast_1](http://v6.cometchat.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/broadcast_1.png)', 'CometChat Server ', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'cometchat-server', '', '', '2013-03-14 16:29:54', '2013-03-14 10:59:54', '', 4290, 'http://www.cometchat.com/documentation/?page_id=4293', 0, 'page', '', 0),
(4298, 1, '2013-03-14 16:41:43', '2013-03-14 11:11:43', '#RED5	\n\nIf you would like to self-host RED5 server,		\n\n* Point your browser to [http://www.red5.org/](http://www.red5.org/)		\n\n* Download and install *Red5 1.0 RC1* on your server from the following link: [http://code.google.com/p/red5/](https://code.google.com/p/red5/)\n(outside support scope)		\n\nIf you would like to use a third-party Red5 host,		\n\n* Sign up with a host like [http://www.red5host.com/](http://www.red5host.com/)		\n\n#Installing Audio/Video Broadcast Plugin with RED5 server		\n* If you don’t have Red5 installed on your server, click the following link:		\n[Steps to install Red5 along with server side packages of CometChat plugins on your server](http://www.cometchat.com/documentation/installing-cometchat/advanced/installing-red5)	\n\n* If you have Red5 up and running on your server, configure CometChat plugins by following the steps listed below:		\n\n**On Linux based systems :**	\n	\n1. Check whether the Red5 server is up and running by visiting the URL: *http://&lt;red5 server URL or IP&gt;:5080*	\n\n2. If the Red5 server is running successfully then go to to webapps directory of your Red5 installation. If RED5 is installed using SVN then in most of the cases the webapp directory is r*ed5_&lt;version&gt;.svn/dist/webapps*.	\n\n3. Download the sever side package for the required plugin by executing the following command: 	\n*wget http://www.cometchat.com/extra/ccred5avbroadcast.tar.gz*	\n\n4. Run the given command to extract the package: *tar -xzf ccred5avbroadcast.tar.gz*		\n\n5. Then delete the tar file by executing the given command: *rm ccred5avbroadcast.tar.gz*	\n\n6. Finally restart the Red5 server.		\n\n7. Thus you have successfully configured Red5 server with server side packages of CometChat plugins on your Linux Systems and now you can test the AVBroadcast plugin on your site.		\n\n**On Windows server:**	\n\n1. Check whether the Red5 server is up and running by visiting the URL: *http://&lt;red5 server URL or IP&gt;:5080*		\n\n2. If the Red5 server is running successfully then download the sever side package for the required plugin from *http://www.cometchat.com/extra/ccred5avbroadcast.zip*	\n\n3. Unzip the ccred5avbroadcast.zip file and move the avbroadcast folder to *webapps* folder of Red5 installation.	\n\n4. Finally restart the Red5 server.		\n\n5. Thus you have successfully configured Red5 server with server side packages of CometChat plugins on your Windows Server and now you can test the AVBroadcast plugin on your site.	\n\n#Adobe FMS\nIf you would like to self-host Adobe FMS server,		\n	\n* Purchase, download and install Adobe FMS on your server (outside support scope)	\n		\nIf you would like to use a third-party Adobe FMS host,	\n\n* Sign up with a host like [http://www.influxis.com/](http://www.influxis.com/)		\n\n#Installing Audio/Video Broadcast Plugin with FMS	\nCreate a folder named ‘*avbroadcast*’ in the applications directory of your FMS.	\n\nFor example, if you are using FMS v4.5 on windows system then you need to create the *avbroadcast* folder in ''*C:Program FilesAdobeFlash Media Server 4.5applications*'' folder.		\n\n#Configuring the Audio/Video Broadcast Plugin\n\n* In the *CometChat Admin Panel* -&gt; Plugins section, add the *Audio/Video Broadcast Plugin* to your live plugins and click on the *config* link besides the name.	\n		\n* Enter the required details.		\n\n* Click on the *Update Settings* button and close the window.	\n		\n![Broadcast](http://v6.cometchat.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/broadcast_2.png)', 'RED5 or FMS (RTMP)', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'red5-or-fms-rtmp', '', '', '2013-03-14 16:41:43', '2013-03-14 11:11:43', '', 4290, 'http://www.cometchat.com/documentation/?page_id=4298', 0, 'page', '', 0),
(4341, 1, '2013-03-13 15:31:24', '2013-03-13 10:01:24', '', 'broadcast_2', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', 'broadcast_2', '', '', '2013-03-13 15:31:24', '2013-03-13 10:01:24', '', 0, 'http://v6.cometchat.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/broadcast_2.png', 0, 'attachment', 'image/png', 0),
(4344, 1, '2013-03-14 16:37:17', '2013-03-14 11:07:17', 'If you would like to self-host Adobe FMS server,		\n\n* Purchase, download and install Adobe FMS on your server (outside support scope)		\n\nIf you would like to use a third-party Adobe FMS host,		\n\n* Sign up with a host like [http://www.influxis.com/](http://www.influxis.com/)		\n\n#Installing Audio/Video Broadcast Plugin with FMS	\n	\nCreate a folder named ‘*avbroadcast*’ in the applications directory of your FMS.\n\nFor example, if you are using FMS v4.5 on windows system then you need to create the *avbroadcast* folder in ‘*C:Program FilesAdobeFlash Media Server 4.5applications*'' folder.		\n\n#Configuring the Audio/Video Broadcast Plugin		\n\n* In the *CometChat Admin Panel* -&gt; *Plugins* section, add the *Audio/Video Broadcast Plugin* to your live plugins and click on the *config* link besides the name.	\n\n* Enter the required details.		\n\n* Click on the *Update Settings* button and close the window.		\n\n![Broadcast Setting](http://v6.cometchat.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/broadcast_3.png)', 'FMS (RTMFP)', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'fms-rtmfp', '', '', '2013-03-14 16:37:17', '2013-03-14 11:07:17', '', 4290, 'http://www.cometchat.com/documentation/?page_id=4344', 0, 'page', '', 0),
