(4439, 1, '2011-05-04 05:25:25', '2011-05-04 05:25:25', 'CometChat can be installed and integrated with virtually any website. If you are integrating CometChat with a software which has a ready integration available, then it should take you about 5 minutes to install CometChat.\n\nIf you are integrating CometChat with a custom site and have programming knowledge, refer to the [Custom Coded Site](http://www.cometchat.com/documentation/installing-cometchat/custom-coded-site) guides. CometChat can be integrated with any PHP, .NET, Classic ASP, Ruby on Rails etc. website. Please make sure that your server must meet the minimum requirements.\n\nIf you are integrating CometChat with a custom site but do not have programming knowledge, simply [purchase](http://www.cometchat.com/buy) our Premium or Platinum Edition and our trained professionals will perform the complete installation and integration of CometChat on your site. We guarantee installation of CometChat on your site.', 'Installing CometChat', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'installing-cometchat', '', '', '2011-05-04 05:25:25', '2011-05-04 05:25:25', '', 0, 'http://www.cometchat.com/documentation/?page_id=2', 88, 'page', '', 0),
(4440, 1, '2011-05-04 12:57:54', '2011-05-04 07:27:54', 'Login to WordPress Administration and go to *Appearances* -&gt; *Editor*. \n\nClick on *Header (header.php)* from the right side panel to edit the header.\n\nImmediately after the opening head tag add the copied code:\n\n	', 'WordPress', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'wordpress', '', '', '2011-05-04 12:57:54', '2011-05-04 07:27:54', '', 146, 'http://www.cometchat.com/documentation/?page_id=29', 139, 'page', '', 0),
(4441, 1, '2011-05-14 12:11:55', '2011-05-14 06:41:55', 'The CometChat Administration Panel is an area which only the administratior can access. From here you can customize most aspects of CometChat.\n\n&gt; Most browser will cache the CometChat code (to improve performance). Thus you need to clear your browser cache to view changes made via Administration Panel.', 'Administration Panel', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'admin', '', '', '2011-05-14 12:11:55', '2011-05-14 06:41:55', '', 0, 'http://www.cometchat.com/documentation/?page_id=54', 92, 'page', '', 0),
(4442, 1, '2011-05-14 13:50:10', '2011-05-14 08:20:10', '#Getting Started\n\nThe administration panel can be accessed at http://www.yoursite.com/cometchat/admin\n\nThe first thing you will see is a prompt to login to access the administration panel. This username and password is different from your site’s login details.\n\n![Login Details](http://v6.cometchat.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/login.png "login")	\n\n#Default Username/Password	\nBy default, the username and password are as follows:\n\nUsername:*cometchat*		\nPassword:*cometchat*		\n\nAfter you login, you will be taken to the dashboard which will show you statistics of CometChat on your site.\n\n![dashboard](http://v6.cometchat.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/dasboard.png "dashboard")', 'Log In to the Admin Panel', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'logging-in', '', '', '2011-05-14 13:50:10', '2011-05-14 08:20:10', '', 4441, 'http://www.cometchat.com/documentation/?page_id=56', 28, 'page', '', 0),
(4581, 1, '2013-04-19 17:40:31', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Cometchat iPhone/Android App can be directly installed on your device. It runs as a standalone application and does not require any browser.\n\nAvailable on all the leading **Android** and **iOS** devices; CometChat iPhone/Android App provides a variety of options like launching one-on-one chats and chatrooms from anywhere.\n\nYou can provide the following guide to your site users:\n\n[CometChat iPhone/Android App](http://v6.cometchat.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/CometChat-iPhone-Android-App.pdf)\n\n(Right click to save the file to your computer)', 'CometChat iPhone/Android App', '', 'pending', 'closed', 'open', '', '', '', '', '2013-04-19 17:40:31', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '', 0, 'http://www.cometchat.com/documentation/?page_id=4581', 0, 'page', '', 0),
(4614, 1, '2013-04-19 16:41:35', '2013-04-19 11:11:35', '', 'CometChat iPhone Android App', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', 'cometchat-iphone-android-app', '', '', '2013-04-19 16:41:35', '2013-04-19 11:11:35', '', 0, 'http://v6.cometchat.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/CometChat-iPhone-Android-App.pdf', 0, 'attachment', 'application/pdf', 0),
(4622, 1, '2013-04-19 17:40:40', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'If you rely on mobile devices for communication, then you don’t need to worry about the same. This is the first ever mobile application that lets the user access CometChat from absolutely anywhere.\n\nAvailable on all the leading mobile devices; CometChat HTML5 Mobile App provides a variety of options like launching one-on-one chats and chatrooms from anywhere.\n\nYou can provide the following guide to your site users:\n\n[CometChat HTML5 Mobile App](http://v6.cometchat.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/CometChat-HTML5-Mobile-App.pdf)\n\n(Right click to save the file to your computer)', 'CometChat HTML5 Mobile App', '', 'pending', 'closed', 'open', '', '', '', '', '2013-04-19 17:40:40', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '', 4581, 'http://www.cometchat.com/documentation/?page_id=4622', 0, 'page', '', 0),
(4624, 1, '2013-04-19 17:22:18', '2013-04-19 11:52:18', '', 'CometChat HTML5 Mobile App', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', 'cometchat-html5-mobile-app', '', '', '2013-04-19 17:22:18', '2013-04-19 11:52:18', '', 0, 'http://v6.cometchat.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/CometChat-HTML5-Mobile-App.pdf', 0, 'attachment', 'application/pdf', 0),
(4625, 1, '2011-05-14 21:00:00', '2011-05-14 15:30:00', '# Modules add new functionality to the CometChat bar.\n\n![Modules]\n(http://v6.cometchat.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2012/04/Capture6.png)\n\n# Live Modules\n\nYou can use your mouse to change the order in which the modules appear on the bar (left-to-right).\n\nThe center section displays all active modules. \nOn the right hand side, the *Available Modules* shows the ready modules that you can integrate instantly.\n\nTo integrate a module, simply click on the *add* button. The selected module will be displayed in the center section.\n\n![Modules - Live Modules]\n(http://v6.cometchat.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2012/04/new+live+modules.png)', 'Modules', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'modules', '', '', '2011-05-14 21:00:00', '2011-05-14 15:30:00', '', 4441, 'http://www.cometchat.com/documentation/?page_id=132', 33, 'page', '', 0),
(4626, 1, '2011-05-14 23:53:22', '2011-05-14 18:23:22', 'With this feature you can apply different themes and change the look and feel of CometChat.\n\n![Themes]\n(http://v6.cometchat.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2012/05/Themes.png)', 'Themes', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'themes', '', '', '2011-05-14 23:53:22', '2011-05-14 18:23:22', '', 4441, 'http://www.cometchat.com/documentation/?page_id=195', 36, 'page', '', 0),
(4627, 1, '2011-05-15 00:01:00', '2011-05-14 18:31:00', '#Setting Up\n\n1. Decide which theme you would like to use as base. \n2. Select the *clone* option next to the theme you would like to use as base.\n3. Type a new name for the theme and click on the *Add Theme* button.\n\n![Create New Theme]\n(http://v6.cometchat.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2012/05/Create+New+Theme+.png)\n\n#Using Theme Editor\n1. Click on *Edit Theme* link next to the theme you want to edit.\n2. If you want to modify the base colors, you can do so by quickly using our inbuilt *Theme Color Editor*.\n3. If you want to modify a specific style, you can manually edit the CSS files.\n\n![Theme Editor]\n(http://v6.cometchat.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2012/05/Theme+Editor.png)\n\n#How to know which style to edit?\n1. Install Firebug for Firefox.\n2. Using the Inspect function select the portion you want to find out the class/ID name.\n3. Add the relevant code to the CSS file.', 'Creating New Theme', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'creating-new-theme', '', '', '2011-05-15 00:01:00', '2011-05-14 18:31:00', '', 4626, 'http://www.cometchat.com/documentation/?page_id=197', 0, 'page', '', 0),
(4628, 1, '2011-05-15 11:10:24', '2011-05-15 05:40:24', 'CometChat''s API enables you to extend the functionality of CometChat. Chat boxes can be launched directly from your website, the bar can be hidden and a lot more.', 'Developers API', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'developers-api', '', '', '2011-05-15 11:10:24', '2011-05-15 05:40:24', '', 0, 'http://www.cometchat.com/documentation/?page_id=200', 109, 'page', '', 0),
(4629, 1, '2011-05-15 16:17:54', '2011-05-15 10:47:54', 'ping() allows you to find out if CometChat has loaded.\n\n# The API\n\nThe ping() function will return true if CometChat has been loaded.\n\n	jqcc.cometchat.ping();\n\n# Sample Code\n\nTo test functionality, wrap the ping() function in a try catch statement.\n\n	document.onload = function() {\n		testload();\n	}\n	\n	function testload(data) {\n		var loaded = 0;\n		try {\n			loaded = jqcc.cometchat.ping();\n		} catch (err) {\n	\n		}\n	\n		if (loaded) {\n			alert(''CometChat has loaded'');\n		}\n	}\n	', 'ping()', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'ping', '', '', '2011-05-15 16:17:54', '2011-05-15 10:47:54', '', 261, 'http://www.cometchat.com/documentation/?page_id=270', 100, 'page', '', 0),
(4630, 1, '2011-05-15 16:28:33', '2011-05-15 10:58:33', 'closeModule() function assists you to dynamically close a module (like Chatrooms, Facebook Fan Page etc.)\n\n# The API\n\nThe input parameter is the module''s short name i.e. the folder name of the module.\n\n	jqcc.cometchat.closeModule(''MODULENAME'');\n\n# Sample Code\n\nA suggested use of this function is to close the Chatrooms module from your webpage.\n\n	<a href="void(0)">Close Chatrooms</a>\n', 'closeModule()', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'closemodule', '', '', '2011-05-15 16:28:33', '2011-05-15 10:58:33', '', 261, 'http://www.cometchat.com/documentation/?page_id=280', 88, 'page', '', 0),
(4631, 1, '2011-05-15 16:48:59', '2011-05-15 11:18:59', '# The API\n\n$userid is a global variable which returns the user ID of the logged in user. If the user is not logged in, the value will be *0*.\n\n# Sample Code\n\n	include_once (cometchat/cometchat_init.php);\n	echo $userid;', '$userid', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'userid', '', '', '2011-05-15 16:48:59', '2011-05-15 11:18:59', '', 294, 'http://www.cometchat.com/documentation/?page_id=297', 63, 'page', '', 0),
(4632, 1, '2011-05-15 16:53:45', '2011-05-15 11:23:45', 'sendAnnouncement() allows you to dynamically send announcements to a particular user.\n\n# The API\n\n	sendAnnouncement($to,$message);\n	\n# Sample Code\n\nIdeal use of this function is to inform the user when an activity happens. Say you have a function which posts messages to a user''s wall.\n\n	function wallPost($fromID, $toID, $fromName, $toName, $message) {\n		// Perform actual wall post\n		\n		include_once (cometchat/cometchat_init.php);\n		sendAnnouncement($toID,"You have a new wall post from ".$fromName);\n	}', 'sendAnnouncement()', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'sendannouncement', '', '', '2011-05-15 16:53:45', '2011-05-15 11:23:45', '', 294, 'http://www.cometchat.com/documentation/?page_id=299', 65, 'page', '', 0),
(4633, 1, '2011-05-16 13:03:32', '2011-05-16 07:33:32', 'If you are using the *default* template, then the header file will be:\n\n*/theme/frontend/default/template/template.html.php*\n\nImmediately after the opening head tag add the copied code:\n\n	', 'phpFox', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'phpfox', '', '', '2011-05-16 13:03:32', '2011-05-16 07:33:32', '', 146, 'http://www.cometchat.com/documentation/?page_id=353', 117, 'page', '', 0),
(4634, 1, '2011-05-16 13:05:51', '2011-05-16 07:35:51', 'Now add the two copied lines to your site header by editing the following file in your SMF installation directory:\n\nFor SMF v1 - \n*index.php*\n\nFor SMF v2 - \n*themes/default/index.template.php*\n\nPaste the two lines immediately after `` tag', 'Simple Machines Forum', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'smf', '', '', '2011-05-16 13:05:51', '2011-05-16 07:35:51', '', 146, 'http://www.cometchat.com/documentation/?page_id=357', 121, 'page', '', 0);
INSERT INTO `ccwp_posts` (`ID`, `post_author`, `post_date`, `post_date_gmt`, `post_content`, `post_title`, `post_excerpt`, `post_status`, `comment_status`, `ping_status`, `post_password`, `post_name`, `to_ping`, `pinged`, `post_modified`, `post_modified_gmt`, `post_content_filtered`, `post_parent`, `guid`, `menu_order`, `post_type`, `post_mime_type`, `comment_count`) VALUES
(4635, 1, '2011-05-23 22:39:14', '2011-05-23 17:09:14', 'To modify the incoming sound alert, only two steps need to be followed:\n\n* Create/find a new beep alert you would like to use. The alert must be in MP3 format.\n* Replace the *cometchat/swf/beep.mp3* with your new file.\n\n![File structure - Change sound alert](http://www.cometchat.com/documentation/media/19.png)\n\n* Delete the *cometchat/swf/sound.swf* file.\n* Rename *cometchat/swf/sound_formp3.swf* to *cometchat/swf/sound.swf*\n* Clear your browser cache completely and hear your new beep play on incoming messages!\n\n', 'Changing incoming message alert beep', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'changing-incoming-message-alert-beep', '', '', '2011-05-23 22:39:14', '2011-05-23 17:09:14', '', 465, 'http://www.cometchat.com/documentation/?page_id=481', 26, 'page', '', 0),
(4636, 1, '2012-05-18 14:55:53', '2012-05-18 09:25:53', 'This feature allows you to communicate with your visitors in real time.  \n\nYou can enter your *announcements* in the *Announcement Text Area* provided and your visitors will get them immediately.\n\nSet the *Show Only to logged-in Users?* to *Yes*, to enable only your *logged in* users to view the announcement.\n\n![New Announcements1]\n(http://v6.cometchat.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2012/04/New+announcement1.png)\n\nTo remove an old announcement, click on the ![Remove](http://v6.cometchat.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2012/04/remove.png) button.\n\n![Remove Announcements]\n(http://v6.cometchat.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2012/04/Remove+announcements.png)\n', 'Announcements', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'announcements', '', '', '2012-05-18 14:55:53', '2012-05-18 09:25:53', '', 4441, 'http://www.cometchat.com/documentation/?page_id=1344', 32, 'page', '', 0),
(4640, 1, '2013-06-25 14:09:03', '2013-06-25 08:39:03', 'The files you need to modify are:\n\nETANO_ROOT_DIRECTORY/skins_site/THEME_NAME/index.html\nETANO_ROOT_DIRECTORY/skins_site/THEME_NAME/frame.html\n\nAdd the CometChat code immediately after &lt;head&gt; tag.\n', 'Etano', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'etano', '', '', '2013-06-25 14:09:03', '2013-06-25 08:39:03', '', 146, 'http://www.cometchat.com/documentation/?page_id=4640', 70, 'page', '', 0),
(4645, 1, '2013-06-25 14:10:18', '2013-06-25 08:40:18', 'The files you need to modify are:\n\nDLE_ROOT_DIRECTORY/templates/THEME_NAME/main.tpl\n\nAdd the CometChat code immediately after &lt;head&gt; tag.\n', 'DLE', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'dle', '', '', '2013-06-25 14:10:18', '2013-06-25 08:40:18', '', 146, 'http://www.cometchat.com/documentation/?page_id=4645', 64, 'page', '', 0),
